<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 7:28PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of north central
Pushmataha, southwestern Latimer and southern Pittsburg Counties
through 800 PM CDT...
At 727 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles south of Hartshorne to 4 miles northwest
of Albion. Movement was west at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Hartshorne...
Krebs...                          Savanna...
Alderson...                       Albion...
Higgins...                        Damon...
Haywood...                        Yanush...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Blanco...
Haileyville...                    Arpelar...
Gowen...                          Sardis...
Dow...                            Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
